<p>I normally use <code>visual block</code> to insert a semicolon at the end of the lines by using: <code>&lt;Ctrl-v&gt;G$A;&lt;Esc&gt;</code>. This works very well. However, when I wanted to delete the semicolons by using the similar keystrokes, <code>&lt;Ctrl-v&gt;G$A&lt;BS&gt;&lt;Esc&gt;</code>, it worked only the first line as following:</p>  <p><strong>Result:</strong></p>  <pre><code>var foo = 1 var bar = 'a'; var baz = 'z'; var foobar = foo + bar; var foobarbaz = foo + bar + baz; </code></pre>  <p><strong>Expected result:</strong></p>  <pre><code>var foo = 1 var bar = 'a' var baz = 'z' var foobar = foo + bar var foobarbaz = foo + bar + baz </code></pre>  <p>What did I do wrong?</p>